714870f-a.title: Manhattan: 96th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
714870f-a.text:
East 96th Street, west from First Ave. Note the Second and Third
Ave. Elevated Lines upon their respective thoroughfares. Partially
seen on the right is the abandoned car barn of the Second Ave. Railroad
Company.
August 13, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

714871f-a.title: Manhattan: 96th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
714871f-a.text:
East 96th Street, north side, east from a point between Second and
First Aves., across the latter to the East River, showing the southeastern
corner of the abandoned carbarn of the Second Ave. Railroad Co. The
structure partially seen on the right is the New York Railways Co. Power
House.
August 13, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
